headline: PacBio, Bristol-Myers Squibb, Oscar Health, Centene, and Molina Healthcare Shares Are Soaring, What You Need To Know
summary: A number of stocks jumped in the afternoon session after a Politico report revealed that the White House plans to pitch a two-year extension of Obamacare subsidies. The proposal would extend subsidies set to expire at the end of the year, with new eligibility limits for individuals with incomes up to 700% of the federal poverty line. headline: Bristol Myers Pops On A 'Surprisingly Positive' Update From Key Rival Bayer
